alittleserver

Simple and secure file server with multiple ports support, SSL and IP banlist.

Installation:
1. Install Go 1.16 or higher
2. Clone repository:
   git clone https://github.com/systemxplore/alittleserver.git
3. Build:
   cd alittleserver
   go build -o alittleserver

Configuration:
1. Ports:
   - Default: 8888, 8889, 8890
   - Edit Ports array in config.go

2. SSL:
   - Generate certificates:
     openssl req -x509 -newkey rsa:4096 -keyout key.pem -out cert.pem -days 365 -nodes
   - Enable in config.go:
     SSL.Enabled = true
     SSL.CertFile = "cert.pem"
     SSL.KeyFile = "key.pem"

3. IP Banlist:
   - Enabled by default
   - Max requests: 50
   - Ban duration: 24 hours
   - Edit in config.go:
     Security.IPBanList.Enabled = true
     Security.IPBanList.MaxRequests = 50
     Security.IPBanList.BanDuration = 24 * time.Hour

4. Security:
   - Blocked paths: /admin, /.git, etc
   - Blocked user agents: bots, crawlers, etc
   - Allowed methods: GET by default
   - Max file size: 100MB
   - Timeout: 30 seconds

Usage:
1. Create files directory:
   mkdir files

2. Start server:
   ./alittleserver

3. Access:
   http://localhost:8888
   http://localhost:8889
   http://localhost:8890

Features:
- Multiple ports support
- SSL/TLS support
- IP banlist with 418 status
- Directory listing
- File size limits
- Security headers
- Path traversal protection
- User agent filtering
- Method filtering
- MIME type detection
- Access logging 